# Social auth and sharing growth rules

- Social login must be implemented through backend OAuth/provider flows, not fake frontend-only buttons.
- Support multiple identity providers per user through an identity/provider account table. Do not add only one `provider` column to the user table.
- Google OAuth should be the first social provider. Apple should be architecture-ready. Facebook and LINE should be provider-ready.
- Do not expose provider tokens or raw OAuth profile data to the frontend.
- Users must not be able to unlink their last login method.
- SNS sharing must be privacy-safe by default. Public share pages must not expose private learning data.
- Share images/postcards should be generated through a reusable renderer service, not arbitrary page screenshots.
- Web Share API, copy link, and download image must work without external SNS SDKs.
- Share templates must be configurable and previewable by admin. Do not hard-code all share cards inside random components.
- Referral rewards must be audited and must go through entitlement/quota services when they affect user limits.
- Track share/referral events for analytics, but minimize personal data.
